    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "from PIL import ImageEnhance\n",
    "\n",
    "from imagemks.rw import rwformat\n",
    "from imagemks.workflows import segment_fluor_cells, measure_fluor_cells, visualize_fluor_cells\n",
    "from imagemks.workflows import default_parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

   ]
  },

    "## Setting up the parameters and loaders"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "path_to_data = '/home/sven/Projects/data/cells/'\n",
    "zoomLev = 2\n",
    "p = default_parameters('muscle')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "nucs_loader = rwformat(path_to_data, prefix='b', ftype='.jpg')\n",
    "cyto_loader = rwformat(path_to_data, prefix='g', ftype='.jpg')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loading the original images"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n = 12\n",
    "\n",
    "N = nucs_loader[n]\n",
    "C = cyto_loader[n]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "small_size = [i//5 for i in N.size]\n",
    "\n",
    "N.resize(small_size)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

   "source": [
    "C.resize(small_size)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Running the Segmentation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "N = np.sum(np.array(N), axis=2)\n",
    "C = np.sum(np.array(C), axis=2)\n",
    "S_N, S_C = segment_fluor_cells(N, C, p['smooth_size'], p['intensity_curve'], p['short_th_radius'], \n",
    "                        p['long_th_radius'], p['min_frequency_to_remove'], p['max_frequency_to_remove'], \n",
    "                        p['max_size_of_small_objects_to_remove'], p['peak_min_distance'],\n",
    "                        p['size_after_watershed_to_remove'], p['cyto_local_avg_size'], zoomLev)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Extracting Measurements"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = measure_fluor_cells(S_N, S_C, pix_size=0.48) #pixel size in micrometers along edge of pixel\n",
    "\n",
    "csi = 4*np.pi * (df['Nuc_Area_um2'].values / df['Nuc_Perimeter_um'].values**2)\n",
    "\n",
    "hist, bins = np.histogram(csi, bins=10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x720 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "colors = ['red','purple']*5\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1, figsize=(10,10))\n",
    "ax.bar(bins[:-1], hist, width=(bins[1]-bins[0]), color=colors)#, c='red')#, align='edge')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Experiment %d'%n, fontsize=24)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Cell Shape Index (CSI)', fontsize=24)\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Cells Count', fontsize=24)\n",
    "for tick in ax.xaxis.get_major_ticks():\n",
    "    tick.label.set_fontsize(18) \n",
    "for tick in ax.yaxis.get_major_ticks():\n",
    "    tick.label.set_fontsize(18) \n",
    "plt.show(fig)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "V_N, E_N = visualize_fluor_cells(S_N, N)\n",
    "\n",
    "V_N = Image.fromarray(V_N).resize(small_size)\n",
    "E_N = Image.fromarray(E_N).resize(small_size)\n",
    "\n",
    "V_C, E_C = visualize_fluor_cells(S_C, C)\n",
    "\n",
    "V_C = Image.fromarray(V_C).resize(small_size)\n",
    "E_C = Image.fromarray(E_C).resize(small_size)"
   ]
  },

    "## Showing borders\n",
    "\n",
    "Borders are important to detect because a good border gives a better measurement. Measurements such as cell shape index (CSI) are important in identifying the type of cell. A CSI of greater than 0.8 shows that we have muscle cells, which is true for experiment 9."
